<pageContent>
    <id><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D060]]></id>
	<title><![CDATA[<Introtext style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold; color:#cc0033; margin:10px -5px 10px 5px; padding:5px 0 5px 5px; background:#e8e8e8; border-bottom:1px solid #333; display:block;">Networking for Results</Introtext>]]></title>
	<title2><![CDATA[]]></title2>
	<instructions><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:bold; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">How do you react to this new information?</welcomeText>]]></instructions>
	<choices>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[1]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>A</b>. Confirm that you’ll meet with Dr. Bennett and Dr. Hayes on Monday. You feel good about your growing relationship with Dr. Bennett, and you know that you can demonstrate a strong case for using your product.</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="5">
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D060_A010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[2]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>B</b>. Call Dennis, your co-promote partner, and see what information you can find out from him about how the other company’s reps position their product. You need to know whether they are currently offering any solutions, such as co-pay cards. </welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="10">
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D060_B010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[3]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[NO]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>C</b>. Plan a meeting with Annie, your District Manager, to get some ideas on how to deal with competitors. She has always been extremely helpful in the past in coming up with ways to deal with these tricky situations. </welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="10">
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="0"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D060_C010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<id><![CDATA[4]]></id>
			<isCorrect><![CDATA[YES]]></isCorrect>
			<choiceText><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px"><b>D</b>. Call Dennis, your co-promote partner, and work with him to build a strategy for the meeting. Dennis has a successful history of working with Sunnydale Psychiatry, and his insights will help you to be fully prepared for the meeting with Dr. Hayes.</welcomeText>]]></choiceText>
			<KPIs totalScore="25">
				<KPI marks="5"><![CDATA[Customer Results Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Sales Progress Score]]></KPI>
				<KPI marks="10"><![CDATA[Trusted Advisor Relationship Score]]></KPI>
			</KPIs>
			<branchTo><![CDATA[OC_SA_R1_D060_D010]]></branchTo>
		</choice>
	</choices>
    <summary><![CDATA[<welcomeText style=" font-family:Helvetica; font-size:12pt; line-height:18pt; text-align:justify; font-weight:normal; color:#333; display:block; margin:0 10px 10px">It is important to leverage your resources and to network broadly when going into a discussion about your product’s disease state. Dennis is the perfect partner to engage here, since you know he also has a good relationship with Sunnydale Psychiatry. Meeting with Dennis beforehand and aligning your strategy for the meeting will ensure that you are prepared for your meeting with Dr. Hayes (Choice D). Choice A is too risky when you have Dennis at your disposal to help you further prepare. Choice B only leverages promotional information from Dennis, which isn’t the only factor to consider, and Dennis may not have that information. Engaging your DM to discuss strategies may not be the best use of your time, since Dennis is closer to the customer and can help build your credibility. Working with your co-promote partner is the best way to demonstrate your role as a trusted advisor and to accelerate the prescribing cycle. Choice D is the best choice.</welcomeText>]]></summary>
</pageContent>